name: bank
description: banking management web application with Spring Boot 3, Spring Security, Spring Cloud and Angular

name: distributed_minispace
description: Microservices-based social network built with .NET8 and ASP .NET Core Blazor WebAssembly, following distributed DDD principles. Scalable social media application CQRS distributed event-driven solution, utilizing SignalR, .NET ML. Features include choreographical Saga patterns, asynchronous messaging, outbox pattern and distributed event sourcing

name: Cloudapp-microservices
description: A web application combining Python and Node.js with a Laravel component.

name: Alloy
description: server application + REST API, microservice architecture

name: crediCheck
description: [In Development] Microservices Application for Credit Analysis | Spring Boot, RabbitMQ, Docker

name: crimsonSky
description: A Real-time Flight Booking microservices application with Java and Spring Cloud

name: micro-react-component
description: micro-react-component is a project designed to create modular React components based on a micro frontend architecture. This project allows different parts of applications to come together to form a flexible and scalable structure.

name: HospitalReferralSystem
description: A Springboot application, using microservices architecture, that enables the client, if authenticated and authorised, send and receive sensitive patient information over a network.

name: python-django-ai-web
description: A Python Django based web application with the frontend made in ReactJS, Typescript and Tailwind made to ship different AI microservices. Currently under development.

name: handspy-pbanalysis
description: HandSpy is a web-based application for management and analysis of mental health aspects of individuals based on their textual productions, both handwritten and typewritten. As of v3, its codebase has been completely re-implemented in a microservice architecture. This repository contains the Pause-Burst Analysis microservice.

name: Scholarly
description: The Scholarly website is a modern, dynamic web application built using a microservices  architecture. It is designed to manage student data efficiently, providing features such as student  profile management,  and collaborative tools.

name: CollegeReviewApp
description: A microservices-based full-stack application where users can sign up, browse college details, and rate colleges on a 5-star scale. Built with Spring Boot microservicesUser, College, and Rating serviceseach backed by its own database (MySQL, PostgreSQL, and MongoDB). The React frontend connects through an API Gateway for seamless and secure access

name: JordiAragonZaragoza.ToDos
description: The goal of this repository is implement the most common used technologies and practice to masterize the best way to develop great applications with .NET using microservices following DDD and Clean Architecture approach

name: identity-management-service
description: The IdentityManagementService is a critical component of the Netflix clone, responsible for managing user identities and authentication processes. This microservice interfaces with Keycloak to handle user registration, login, profile management, and secure access to various application features.

name: Azure_DevOps_CI-CD_Project
description: This project demonstrates a full CI/CD pipeline using Azure DevOps for a containerized voting application with microservices. It includes automated image builds, pushes to Azure Container Registry, and GitOps-based deployments to an Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS) cluster using ArgoCD.

name: taxi-management-system
description: This project is a full-stack application built with Laravel and Flutter that implements JWT-based authentication, WebSocket for real-time updates, and a microservice-inspired architecture. Users can register, login, and perform CRUD operations on cars, with real-time notifications available for certain actions.
